.Dd $Mdocdate: May 17 2026 $
.Dt CERTES 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm certes
.Nd certificate authority and role attributor
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm certes
.Op Fl debug
.Op Fl config Ar path
.Ar command
.Op Ar arguments
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is an
.Xr mdrd 8
backend service that acts as a certificate authority and role attributor.
It issues X.509 certificates carrying a custom
.Dq roles
extension, allowing services to grant privileges based on a client
certificate's roles in addition to identity.
.Pp
The same binary runs in two modes:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Sy authority
The signing side, holding the CA key and the
.Xr sqlite3 1
certificate database.
Run via
.Nm mdrd
using the
.Cm mdrd-backend
command.
.It Sy agent
A client that bootstraps against an authority to obtain a certificate
and renews it automatically.
Also run via
.Nm mdrd
using the
.Cm mdrd-backend
command.
.El
.Pp
Subcommands not run via
.Xr mdrd 8
are administrative one-shots: bootstrap setup, certificate inspection,
role and SAN modifications, revocation, request signing, and CRL refresh.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "-config path"
.It Fl debug
Do not fork; print errors to standard error.
.It Fl config Ar path
Use
.Ar path
as the configuration file instead of the default
.Pa /etc/certes/certes.conf .
The environment variable
.Ev CERTES_CONF
overrides the default but is itself overridden by this flag.
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm mdrd-backend
Run as an
.Xr mdrd 8
backend.
This is the long-running daemon mode used for both authority and agent
roles; the role is inferred from the loaded certificate's
.Dq roles
extension.
.It Cm init
Generate the agent's initial private key and a temporary self-signed
certificate.
Required once per agent before
.Xr mdrd 8
can start the backend.
On subsequent startups the agent uses the existing key and the
authority-signed certificate written during bootstrap.
.It Cm init-db
Create the authority's certificate database and exit.
Run once on the authority host before starting
.Xr mdrd 8 .
.It Cm bootstrap-setup Oo Fl cn Ar commonName Oc Oo Fl san Ar SAN Oc Oo Fl role Ar role Oc Oo Fl cert_expiry Ar seconds Oc Oo Fl timeout Ar seconds Oc
Create a bootstrap entry on the authority and print its base64
bootstrap key on standard output.
The key is single-use: an agent presents it once during bootstrap to
obtain a signed certificate with the SANs and roles given here.
.Pp
Options:
.Bl -tag -width "-cert_expiry"
.It Fl cn Ar commonName
Subject CN to assign to the issued certificate.
If omitted, the agent's REQ subject is preserved.
.It Fl san Ar SAN
Add a Subject Alternative Name.
May be repeated.
SANs are
.Xr X509v3 7
strings such as
.Sy DNS:host.example.com
or
.Sy IP:192.0.2.1 .
.It Fl role Ar role
Add a role to the issued certificate.
May be repeated.
Roles must be alphanumeric.
The
.Sy agent
role is always added implicitly.
.It Fl cert_expiry Ar seconds
Certificate lifetime, in seconds.
Default: 604800 (7 days).
.It Fl timeout Ar seconds
Validity of the bootstrap entry itself, in seconds.
Default: 600.
After this period the entry is purged and the bootstrap key becomes
unusable.
.El
.Pp
Must be run on the authority host with a certificate carrying the
.Sy bootstrap
role.
.It Cm cert Oo Fl serial Ar hex Oc Oo Fl find Ar pattern Oc
Display a certificate from the authority's database, or list serials
whose subject matches a pattern.
With
.Fl serial ,
prints the full certificate including roles and SANs.
With
.Fl find ,
prints serial, subject, and flags for each match.
.Pp
Requires a certificate with the
.Sy certadmin
role.
.It Cm role Fl serial Ar hex Oo Fl add Ar role Oc Oo Fl del Ar role Oc
Modify the roles on an existing certificate in the authority's
database.
The
.Fl add
and
.Fl del
flags may be repeated.
Note that this modifies the database record but does not re-issue the
certificate; the client must renew to get a certificate with the new
roles.
.Pp
Requires the
.Sy certadmin
role.
.It Cm san Fl serial Ar hex Oo Fl add Ar SAN Oc Oo Fl del Ar SAN Oc
Like
.Cm role ,
but for Subject Alternative Names.
.It Cm revoke Fl serial Ar hex
Revoke a certificate by serial.
The revocation is reflected in the next CRL generation.
.Pp
Requires the
.Sy certadmin
role.
.It Cm sign-req Fl in Ar file Fl out Ar file Oo Fl cert_expiry Ar seconds Oc Oo Fl role Ar role Oc Oo Fl server_auth Oc Oo Fl copy_sans Oc
Sign a PEM-encoded X.509 certificate signing request and write the
resulting certificate.
Unlike
.Cm bootstrap-setup ,
this is a one-shot operation that does not provision the recipient as
an agent.
.Pp
Options:
.Bl -tag -width "-cert_expiry"
.It Fl in Ar file
Path to the PEM-encoded REQ.
.It Fl out Ar file
Where to write the resulting PEM-encoded certificate.
.It Fl cert_expiry Ar seconds
Certificate lifetime, in seconds.
Default: 604800 (7 days).
.It Fl role Ar role
Add a role to the certificate.
May be repeated.
.It Fl server_auth
Add the
.Sy serverAuth
extended key usage in addition to
.Sy clientAuth .
.It Fl copy_sans
Copy SANs from the REQ into the issued certificate.
.El
.Pp
Requires the
.Sy certadmin
role.
.It Cm update-crls
Fetch updated CRLs from the configured authority and write them under
.Va crl_path .
The agent does this automatically on its CRL refresh interval;
this command forces an immediate refresh.
.Pp
Primarily intended for
.Sy certadmin
operators running
.Nm
from a workstation: their CLI invocations of
.Cm cert , role , san , revoke ,
and
.Cm sign-req
validate the authority's certificate against the locally-stored CRLs,
so running
.Cm update-crls
beforehand ensures those checks use current revocation data.
.El
.Sh ROLES
The
.Dq roles
extension is an authority-defined OID (default
.Sy 1.3.6.1.4.1.35910.3.1 )
encoding a list of alphanumeric strings.
Roles used internally by
.Nm
are:
.Bl -tag -width "certadmin"
.It Sy authority
The certificate belongs to an authority.
Authorities trust each other when forwarding dialback challenges and
fetching CRLs.
.It Sy bootstrap
Permitted to call
.Cm bootstrap-setup
on an authority.
.It Sy certadmin
Permitted to call
.Cm cert , role , san , revoke ,
and
.Cm sign-req
on an authority.
.It Sy agent
Implicitly granted to every bootstrapped agent.
Permitted to request its own certificate renewal.
.It Sy caproxy
A trusted proxy in front of an authority.
.El
.Pp
Applications may define their own roles freely.
.Sh DEPLOYMENT
The two modes have different filesystem layouts.
.Ss Agents
.Nm
rewrites
.Va cert_file
on every successful bootstrap and renewal, typically every few days.
The cert, key, lock file, agent socket, and CRL directory must
therefore live under a writable state directory such as
.Pa /var/lib/certes
.Pq Debian
or
.Pa /var/certes ,
not under
.Pa /etc .
.Pp
.Nm
and
.Xr mdrd 8
typically run as the same user on agent hosts, and both must be able to
read
.Va cert_file
and
.Va crl_path .
.Xr mdrd 8
loads the cert at startup and again whenever it detects a change.
.Ss Authorities
On authority hosts,
.Nm
and
.Xr mdrd 8
usually run as separate users, each with its own
.Va cert_file
and
.Va key_file .
.Nm
holds the CA signing key
.Pq Pa ca_key.pem ,
which is read once and never rewritten;
.Xr mdrd 8
holds a server cert
.Pq Pa proxy_cert.pem
issued by the authority itself.
Both can live under
.Pa /etc/certes
since neither file is touched at runtime by its owning process.
The
.Va certdb_path
SQLite database and the
.Va crl_path
directory are written by
.Nm
and must be under a writable state directory.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width CERTES_CONF
.It Ev CERTES_CONF
Path to the configuration file.
Overridden by
.Fl config .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/etc/certes/certes.conf"
.It Pa /etc/certes/certes.conf
Default configuration file.
.It Pa /etc/certes/ca_cert.pem
Authority's signing certificate.
.It Pa /etc/certes/ca_key.pem
Authority's signing key.
.It Pa /etc/certes/root.pem
Root CA certificate used to validate the authority.
.It Pa /var/certes/certdb.sqlite
Authority's certificate database.
.It Pa /var/certes/crls
Directory of CRLs, one file per issuing authority.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Create a bootstrap entry that allows an agent to obtain a 5-minute
certificate with one SAN:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
# certes bootstrap-setup -san DNS:certes.example.com -cert_expiry 300
.Ed
.Pp
On the agent host, write the printed key to the
.Va bootstrap_key
field of
.Pa certes.conf ,
generate the initial key, then start
.Xr mdrd 8 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
# certes init
# mdrd -c /etc/certes/mdrd.conf
.Ed
.Pp
Sign a REQ for a user, granting the
.Sy certadmin
role and
.Sy serverAuth
extended usage:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
# certes sign-req -in req.pem -out cert.pem \e
    -role certadmin -server_auth
.Ed
.Pp
Force the agent to refresh CRLs from the authority:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ certes update-crls
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr openssl 1 ,
.Xr sqlite3 1 ,
.Xr x509 1 ,
.Xr certes.conf 5 ,
.Xr mdrd 8
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Pascal Lalonde Aq Mt plalonde@overnet.ca
